Since the argument to `zip()` uses [`IntoIterator`](trait.IntoIterator.html "trait std::iter::IntoIterator"), we can pass anything that can be converted into an [`Iterator`](trait.Iterator.html "trait std::iter::Iterator"), not just an [`Iterator`](trait.Iterator.html "trait std::iter::Iterator") itself. For example, slices (`&[T]`) implement [`IntoIterator`](trait.IntoIterator.html "trait std::iter::IntoIterator"), and so can be passed to `zip()` directly:

```
let s1 = &[1, 2, 3];
let s2 = &[4, 5, 6];

let mut iter = s1.iter().zip(s2);

assert_eq!(iter.next(), Some((&1, &4)));
assert_eq!(iter.next(), Some((&2, &5)));
assert_eq!(iter.next(), Some((&3, &6)));
assert_eq!(iter.next(), None);
```

