1.0.0 ¬∑ [source](https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.80.0/src/core/iter/traits/iterator.rs.html#1881-1883)

Borrows an iterator, rather than consuming it.

This is useful to allow applying iterator adapters while still retaining ownership of the original iterator.

##### [¬ß](#examples-29)Examples

```
let mut words = ["hello", "world", "of", "Rust"].into_iter();

// Take the first two words.
let hello_world: Vec<_> = words.by_ref().take(2).collect();
assert_eq!(hello_world, vec!["hello", "world"]);

// Collect the rest of the words.
// We can only do this because we used `by_ref` earlier.
let of_rust: Vec<_> = words.collect();
assert_eq!(of_rust, vec!["of", "Rust"]);
```

