1.0.0 ¬∑ [source](https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.80.0/src/core/iter/traits/iterator.rs.html#3157-3160)

Returns the maximum element of an iterator.

If several elements are equally maximum, the last element is returned. If the iterator is empty, [`None`](about:blank/option/enum.Option.html#variant.None "variant std::option::Option::None") is returned.

Note that [`f32`](../primitive.f32.html "primitive f32")/[`f64`](../primitive.f64.html "primitive f64") doesn‚Äôt implement [`Ord`](../cmp/trait.Ord.html "trait std::cmp::Ord") due to NaN being incomparable. You can work around this by using [`Iterator::reduce`](about:blank/trait.Iterator.html#method.reduce "method std::iter::Iterator::reduce"):

```
assert_eq!(
    [2.4, f32::NAN, 1.3]
        .into_iter()
        .reduce(f32::max)
        .unwrap(),
    2.4
);
```

