Reverses an iterator‚Äôs direction.

Usually, iterators iterate from left to right. After using `rev()`, an iterator will instead iterate from right to left.

This is only possible if the iterator has an end, so `rev()` only works on [`DoubleEndedIterator`](trait.DoubleEndedIterator.html "trait std::iter::DoubleEndedIterator")s.

