[Lexicographically](about:blank/cmp/trait.Ord.html#lexicographical-comparison "trait std::cmp::Ord") compares the elements of this [`Iterator`](trait.Iterator.html "trait std::iter::Iterator") with those of another with respect to the specified comparison function.

##### [¬ß](#examples-64)Examples

```
#![feature(iter_order_by)]

use std::cmp::Ordering;

let xs = [1.0, 2.0, 3.0, 4.0];
let ys = [1.0, 4.0, 9.0, 16.0];

assert_eq!(
    xs.iter().partial_cmp_by(&ys, |&x, &y| x.partial_cmp(&y)),
    Some(Ordering::Less)
);
assert_eq!(
    xs.iter().partial_cmp_by(&ys, |&x, &y| (x * x).partial_cmp(&y)),
    Some(Ordering::Equal)
);
assert_eq!(
    xs.iter().partial_cmp_by(&ys, |&x, &y| (2.0 * x).partial_cmp(&y)),
    Some(Ordering::Greater)
);
```

